The <strong><code>:has()</code></strong> CSS <a href="/en-US/docs/Web/CSS/Pseudo-classes">pseudo-class</a> represents an element if any of the selectors passed as parameters (relative to the <a href="/en-US/docs/Web/CSS/:scope" title="The :scope CSS pseudo-class represents elements that are a reference point for selectors to match against."><code>:scope</code></a> of the given element), match at least one element.